race.comment: PATYEP (2) improved last start finding a couple better over 1200m after being in the firing line on the bend. Suitably placed and over a bit shorter will take plenty of betting with Todd back on. SNAPPY SWEETHEART (3) had been in top form landing two consecutive wins before a plainer run last time. Inclined to forgive that and she has a 3kg claimer aboard today and she's sure to use the inside gate.  A big chance to bounce. RED EXTREME (6) resumed in better grade and needed the outing. She's still a Maiden but fitter can work into a minor slot. ONE WAY RIDE (5) has switched from a Victorian stable on a 14-day return. She's been very disappointing her last three but has the blinkers on for the first time and she displayed talent early doors. Draws in side and keep an eye on the betting. BERKELEY BAY (4) is also ex-Vic and resumes. Will need it on what we've seen.
